JDK Settings : 
$> /usr/libexec/java_home -V

To set the correct JDK location in IntelliJ
- Go to File/Project Settings/
- Set the correct JDK Path

If you set the correct JDK Paths, you will be able to : 
- See populated correct locations in File/Project Settings/Platform Settings
- Able to navigate to JDK source code

Installing Java on Mac OS X
- JRE - install via System Preferences -> Java
- JDK - download from Oracle and install ( see instructions for removing old versions and making latest default )
- Unlimited Strenght JCE - download from Oracle and install